                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.51 P 92/–: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Change in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Goold</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-08-25T15:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 25, 1927—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>28. Your 54, August 25, 11 a.m. The policy outlined in Department’s telegram No.
                    20, April 26, 6 p.m., remains unchanged. This Government cannot favor the
                    flotation of any loan on the American market for the benefit of a government
                    which has not funded its American debt.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
